  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Opportunities and jobs to villagers in Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Afrodescendent community from La Boquilla has lived in extreme poverty over generations due to structural racism, slavery and inequality. They really want a better life, but struggle with how to do so in a city with so much unemployment. English is our bestbet, because in Cartagena international tourism is growing and there is a lack of local people who speak English. Through our program they will receive 200hrs of English lessons over 1yr, which will help them to communicate and find a job.</narrative>
  </description>
